{
  "texts": [
    "Reference [40] describes a DQN-based framework that dynamically orchestrates service function chains (SFCs).",
    "This framework decides where to place VNFs (in the cloud or at the edge) and how to connect them to meet real-time traffic demands.",
    "The DQN agent takes into account the traffic flow rate of services and the status of VNFs when making decisions.",
    "The framework defines the action space as the number of VNFs to activate and the traffic flow to schedule.",
    "The performance of the framework was evaluated using heterogeneous NFV/MEC-enabled IoT network scenarios emulated with the network tool."
  ]
}